title.narrative: Regional Agricultural Development Program- East (RADP East)

description.narrative: (Afghanistan): The Regional Agricultural Development Program East (RADP-E) aims to foster sustainable economic growth in eastern Afghanistan by strengthening the competitiveness of agricultural value chains. Through technical assistance, RADP-E will expand the number of agribusinesses that can participate in selected value chains; help enterprises upgrade their products and services; improve their operations, allowing them to attract investment to be used to further improve their business; increase the commercial viability of agribusinesses; and increase women's participation in agricultural value chains and agribusinesses. By improving market linkages, RADP-E will increase the domestic and export sales of agricultural products, which directly contributes to the Integrated Country Strategy Mission Goal to promote economic prosperity through private sector led exports. .
